## BLOC B - Regulateur 5V [MODIFIE v4.9]

### ⚠️ ATTENTION CRITIQUE — PINOUT DIFFERENT DU MCP1702! ⚠️

**Composant:** NCV2931AZ-5.0G (ON Semiconductor, TO-92, AEC-Q100)

**Broches NCV2931 TO-92:** 1=Vout, 2=GND, 3=Vin

**Comparaison brochages (VUE FACE PLATE, pattes vers bas):**

```
         MCP1702              NCV2931
        ---------            ---------
       |    _    |          |    _    |
       |   (_)   |          |   (_)   |
       |         |          |         |
       |_________|          |_________|
        |   |   |            |   |   |
        1   2   3            1   2   3
       GND Vout Vin        Vout GND Vin
```

**⚠️ PINS 1 ET 2 INVERSES! NE PAS MONTER COMME MCP1702!**

**Cablage NCV2931:**

[+12V_PROT] -> NCV2931 Vin (pin 3)

NCV2931 GND (pin 2) -> [GND_STAR]

NCV2931 Vout (pin 1) -> [+5V_LOG]

**Specs NCV2931AZ-5.0G:**

- Vout: 5.0V +/-3.8%
- Vin operating: 3.0V - 26V
- Vin transient max: **60V** (load dump protection integree)
- Dropout: 600mV @ 100mA (typ)
- Iq: 1mA (typ)
- Iout max: 100mA
- Package: TO-92 THT
- Qualification: **AEC-Q100** (automotive)

**Justification upgrade v4.9:**

```
PROBLEME MCP1702:
- TVS 1.5KE18CA clamp = 25.2V @ 60A
- MCP1702 Vin abs max = 14.5V
- Load dump -> 25.2V sur Vin -> DESTRUCTION IMMEDIATE
- Cascade: court-circuit Vin-Vout -> 25V sur +5V_LOG -> destruction logique

SOLUTION NCV2931:
- NCV2931 Vin transient = 60V
- Marge: (60V - 25.2V) / 60V = 58%
- Load dump protection integree (shutdown automatique >26V continu)
- AEC-Q100 qualifie automobile
```

**Verification cold crank:**

```
Vin_min = 6V (demarreur)
Vdrop_max = 600mV @ 100mA
Vin_required = 5V + 0.6V = 5.6V
Marge: (6V - 5.6V) = 400mV OK
```

**Verification thermique (Ta=50C coffre):**

```
P_diss = (14.4V - 5V) x 0.05A = 0.47W
Rth_ja TO-92 = 200C/W
Tj = 50 + (0.47 x 200) = 144C < 150C OK (marge serree)
```

**Decouplages:**

VIN: 100nF X7R 50V || 10uF Low-ESR 50V

VOUT: 100nF X7R 25V + 10uF + 47uF Low-ESR 25V (ESR <= 0.3 Ohm obligatoire)

